he face of war, their desire for full citizenship, the complex loyalties that shaped their actions, and the inspiring and heartbreaking results of their choices-- choices that still echo through the United States today. Contributors: Stephen D. Engle, William McKee Evans, David T. Gleeson, Andrea Mehrländer, Joseph P. Reidy, Robert N. Rosen, and Susannah J. Ural.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy19th century. 0aMinoritieszUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy19th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / Civil War Period (1850-1877).2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aAnglo-Saxon.  aCitizens.  aCivil.  aGrounded.  aProtestant.  abook.  acitizenry.  adominant.  aeffort.  aexperiences.  aexperts.  aextensive.  afields.  afirst.  agather.  ainto.  alived.  anineteenth-century.  aoutside.  apopulations.  aresearch.  arespective.  atheir.  atogether.  awartime.  awhite.1 aEngle, Stephen D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, William McKee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGleeson, David T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMehrländer, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReidy, Joseph P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosen, Robert N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUral, Susannah J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUral, Susannah J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081478569040uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814785690.001